<hl>
<seg id=1> Detroit's 25-floor high building was razed to the ground in 30 seconds. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Detroit) The 107 year old Harrison Building became a huge pile of ruble in only 30 seconds the day before yesterday. </seg>
<seg id=3> This 25 floor building was built with reinforcing steel bars. It was the highest building that was ever dynamited with the positioned shaped charges. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The Harrison building was once the largest retail store in the world, and also was a Detroit attraction. </seg>
<seg id=5> With the sound of the 1215 kg shaped charges detonating explosions, the building became 360 million kg of gravel. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> At 5:45pm local time, a series of explosions inside the Harrison building were initiated. The huge amounts of thick dust and debris from the building's exploding completely enveloped the nearby spectators. </seg>
<seg id=7> A city citizen said that: " I never expected to be covered up with so much dust and debris." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> While the building was collapsing, some people cheered loudly, and others had tears in their eyes, as they would not ever see this same building again. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> In the 50's at the height of its power and splendor, there were about 100,000 people shopping in the Harrison building every day. </seg>
<seg id=10> Then and there, some famous movie stars such as Jiabao and Paike had also been here. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=11> The Detroit Mayor, Arche said to the public that, the government wanted to give the opportunity of operating the detonator to the city citizens in order to raise 150,000 US dollars in funds for charity. </seg>
<seg id=12> However, nobody wanted to turn on the detonation switch to destroy this building, because the Harrison building was the glory of Detroit in former days. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=13> A man who wanted to protect this building said that: " This is a heartbreaking thing." </seg>
</p>
